Relax Data Science Challenge¶

Data Sources:¶

takehome_users(information about a given user and how their account was created) takehome_user_engagement (row for each day a user logged into the product)

Defining an "adopted user" as a user who has logged into the product on three separate days in at least one seven-day period, identify which factors predict future user adoption.¶

for name, group in df_grouped:
    n = len(group)
    if n >= 3:
        tg = group['time_stamp'].drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)
        for i in range(n-2):
            delta = tg[i+2] - tg[i]
            if delta.days < 7:
                #print('user_id=', name)
                df_u.loc[df_u['object_id']==name, 'adopted'] = 1
                break

Data wrangling¶

Here I need to prepare the data set for use with the ML models, and manipulate the datetime objects into new columns that are numeric and can be used by ML.

I'll be dropping the features which cannot have any predictive power: name, email, etc.

Finally, I'll create some dummy variables from a few other features that are categorical.

In [494]:
# create a feature of user history
# convert both time features into datetime
df_u['creation_time'] = pd.to_datetime(
    df_u['creation_time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
df_u['last_session_creation_time'] = pd.to_datetime(
    df_u['last_session_creation_time'], unit='s')
# calculate user history, defined as number of days between account creation and last use
df_u['history'] = df_u['last_session_creation_time'] - df_u['creation_time']
df_u['history'] = df_u['history'].dt.days
# calculate account age, defined as number of days since account creation and now
# Let's use the latest date in creation_time
latest = max(df_u['creation_time'])
df_u['account_age'] = latest - df_u['creation_time']
df_u['account_age'] = df_u['account_age'].dt.days
# drop the two original columns
df_u = df_u.drop(['creation_time', 'last_session_creation_time'], axis=1)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
def plot_hist_days(df, col, xlabel):
    _ = sns.histplot(df.loc[data['adopted']==1, col], 
                 bins=30, alpha=0.3, color='b', label='adopted')
    _ = sns.histplot(df.loc[data['adopted']==0, col], 
                 bins=30, alpha=0.3, color='r', label='non adopted user')
    _ = plt.yscale('log')
    _ = plt.legend()
    _ = plt.xlabel(xlabel)
    _ = plt.ylabel('No. of users')
    _ = plt.yticks([1, 10, 100, 1000], ['1', '10', '100', '1000'])
plot_hist_days(data, 'history', 'user history(days)')
